"v.改变，更改 【英】 v. 改变, 更改(cause to become different) 【考】 friable : crumble / malleable : alter(易碎的容易破碎/可 变的容易改变) 【记】 alter本身就是词根: 其他的,改变状态 【同】 派生词: alteration (n.改变，变更 change)近形词: altercation(争吵); alternation(交替) v. 改变(改服装使之更为合身); 阉割(割除动物, 如猫或狗的卵巢) 【例】These clothes must be altered 这些衣服得修改. The weather alters almost daily 天气几乎天天变化. 【参】altercation(n 争论, 口角); alternation(n 交替, 间隔) 【类】friable: crumble = malleable: alter易碎的容易破碎 = 有延展性的的容易改变 【记】源自other，al=o, t=th alter (v.)  late 14c., ""to change (something),"" from Old French alterer ""change, alter,"" from Medieval Latin alterare ""to change,"" from Latin alter ""the other (of the two),"" from PIE *al- ""beyond"" (see alias (adv.)) + comparative suffix -ter (as in other). Intransitive sense ""to become otherwise"" first recorded 1580s. Related: Altered; altering."
